item.title: Residents told to evacuate after crash causes explosion on Bruce Highway in Queensland
item.description:
Male truck driver airlifted to hospital from Bororen, 400km north of Brisbane, as ammonium nitrate spill sparks 2.5km exclusion zone

  • Follow our Australia news live blog for latest updates
  • Get our breaking news email, free app or daily news podcast

People have been ordered to evacuate from the site of a fiery crash after a semi-trailer carrying chemicals and a ute collided on a major highway, and the truck exploded.

An emergency alert was issued advising residents in an exclusion zone to “leave immediately” following the Bruce Highway crash at Bororen, 400km north of Brisbane, early on Friday.

item.title: Tall ship Leeuwin dismasted in container ship crash off Fremantle
item.description:
Two night watchmen taken to hospital after three-masted 1850s-style sailing ship hit by 332-metre vessel

  • Follow our Australia news live blog for latest updates
  • Get our breaking news email, free app or daily news podcast

A container ship has dismasted the tall ship Leeuwin and clipped a portside museum building while attempting to berth in Fremantle.

Two workers aboard Australia’s largest sail-training tall ship, which has an overall length of 55 metres, were taken to hospital.
